[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":246},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F":222,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F24\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x\u002F":231},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20200124\u002F3404456418\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":205,"date":206,"description":19,"extension":207,"lang":208,"meta":209,"navigation":210,"path":211,"readingMinutes":212,"seo":213,"standalone":214,"stem":215,"tags":216,"tldr":219,"updated":219,"url":220,"__hash__":221},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Finstall-nvm-on-mac-os-x.md","Installing nvm on Mac OS X","7034456184",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":200},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,35,38,55,63,70,77,80,86,97,119,122,131,138,143,146,168,177,181,196],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"As a frontend engineer who touches Node.js, nvm is a must-install. On Mac it's a bit more annoying than Windows — there's no dedicated installer.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"installing-nvm","Installing nvm",[17,25,26,27,34],{},"The ",[28,29,33],"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fnvm-sh\u002Fnvm#troubleshooting-on-macos",[32],"nofollow","official nvm repo"," does have a tutorial, but I'll just write down what I did.",[17,36,37],{},"Open iTerm2 and run:",[39,40,45],"pre",{"className":41,"code":42,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","curl -o- https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fnvm-sh\u002Fnvm\u002Fv0.35.2\u002Finstall.sh | bash\n","cmd","",[46,47,48],"code",{"__ignoreMap":44},[49,50,53],"span",{"class":51,"line":52},"line",1,[49,54,42],{},[17,56,57,58,62],{},"Heads up — don't use Homebrew to install it (",[59,60,61],"del",{},"at least that's what the references say",") to avoid issues.",[17,64,65,66,69],{},"After that command, nvm gets installed to ",[46,67,68],{},"~\u002F.nvm",". If that's not obvious — open Finder, navigate to your home directory, and you might see this:",[17,71,72],{},[73,74],"img",{"alt":75,"src":76},"Finder","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002Frayxu_%E5%92%8C_Mac-OS-X-%E5%AE%89%E8%A3%9D-nvm_md_%E2%80%94_WelcomeWebWorld.png",[17,78,79],{},"Basically you won't see anything. To make your terminal or iTerm2 actually run nvm, you need to adjust the environment variable in the relevant shell config file. Normally those files are hidden, so in Finder press Command + Shift + . to show hidden files.",[17,81,82],{},[73,83],{"alt":84,"src":85},"Hidden files","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-01-24%2019.13.53.png",[17,87,88,89,92,93,96],{},"By default the terminal uses ",[46,90,91],{},".bash_profile",", and iTerm2 uses ZSH, which is ",[46,94,95],{},".zshrc",". Just add the following environment variables to the end of the relevant file:",[39,98,100],{"className":41,"code":99,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"export NVM_DIR=\"$HOME\u002F.nvm\"\n[ -s \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fnvm.sh\" ] && \\. \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fnvm.sh\"  # This loads nvm\n[ -s \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fbash_completion\" ] && \\. \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fbash_completion\"  # This loads nvm bash_completion\n",[46,101,102,107,113],{"__ignoreMap":44},[49,103,104],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,105,106],{},"export NVM_DIR=\"$HOME\u002F.nvm\"\n",[49,108,110],{"class":51,"line":109},2,[49,111,112],{},"[ -s \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fnvm.sh\" ] && \\. \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fnvm.sh\"  # This loads nvm\n",[49,114,116],{"class":51,"line":115},3,[49,117,118],{},"[ -s \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fbash_completion\" ] && \\. \"$NVM_DIR\u002Fbash_completion\"  # This loads nvm bash_completion\n",[17,120,121],{},"That'll point to nvm and you can use it.",[17,123,124,125,127,128,130],{},"(If you don't have ",[46,126,91],{}," or ",[46,129,95],{},", just create one.)",[17,132,133,134,137],{},"Finally, open your terminal and run ",[46,135,136],{},"nvm"," to see the available commands.",[17,139,140],{},[73,141],{"alt":136,"src":142},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-01-24%2019.19.07.png",[17,144,145],{},"Common nvm commands:",[147,148,149,156,162],"ul",{},[150,151,152,155],"li",{},[46,153,154],{},"nvm install [node version]"," — install a specific Node version",[150,157,158,161],{},[46,159,160],{},"nvm list"," — list installed versions",[150,163,164,167],{},[46,165,166],{},"nvm use [node version]"," — switch to a specific Node version (must be installed)",[17,169,170,171,176],{},"For the Windows version of nvm install, see ",[28,172,175],{"href":173,"rel":174},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20200107\u002F3738078915\u002F",[32],"this post (article in Mandarin)",".",[12,178,180],{"id":179},"references","References",[147,182,183,189],{},[150,184,185],{},[28,186,188],{"href":30,"rel":187},[32],"Troubleshooting on macOS",[150,190,191],{},[28,192,195],{"href":193,"rel":194},"https:\u002F\u002Fmedium.com\u002F@toumasaya\u002Fnode-js-%E7%92%B0%E5%A2%83%E8%A8%AD%E5%AE%9A-for-mac-a2628836feaf",[32],"Node.js 環境設定-for mac",[197,198,199],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":44,"searchDepth":109,"depth":109,"links":201},[202,203,204],{"id":14,"depth":109,"text":